| Feature          | Abstract Class                             | Interface                                          |
| ---------------- | ------------------------------------------ | ------------------------------------------------ |
| Keyword          | `abstract class`                           | `interface`                                      |
| Object Creation  | ❌ Cannot create object                     | ❌ Cannot create object                           |
| Constructor      | ✅ Allowed                                  | ❌ Not Allowed                                    |
| Variables        | Instance variables allowed                 | By default `public static final`                 |
| Methods          | Abstract + Concrete methods                | Abstract methods, `default` and `static` methods |
| Inheritance      | A class can extend only one abstract class | A class can implement multiple interfaces        |
| Access Modifiers | Any access modifier                        | Methods are public by default                    |
| Use Case         | Common behavior + partial implementation   | Contract / capability                            |



